{'content': 'function calculate_fitness(agent, model)
    total_fitness = 0.0
    N = model.properties[:N]
    K = model.properties[:K]
    for i in 1:N
        # Select the fitness landscape for the i-th element.
        landscape_i = model.properties[:landscape][i]
        #println("Landscape of the i element is $(landscape_i)")
        # With the ternary operator, we are changing the binary string created in state = rand(Bool, N)
        # to an array of 0s and 1s. First, the state of the element and then the state of the other elements based on K value
        binary_iterator = [agent.state[i] ? 1 : 0, [(agent.state[mod(i+j-1, N)+1] ? 1 : 0) for j in 1:K]...]
        #println("Binary iterator is $(binary_iterator)")
        # Convert the binary string to an index.
        index = parse(Int, join(binary_iterator), base = 2) + 1
        #println("Index is $(index)")
        # Add the fitness contribution of the i-th element to the total fitness.
        total_fitness += landscape_i[index]
        #println("total fitness is $(total_fitness)")
    end
    # Return the average fitness.
    agent.fitness = total_fitness / N
    #println("Agent fitness is $(agent.fitness), because $(total_fitness) / $(N))")
    return agent.fitness
end', 'role': 'user'}
